Volvo to build truck plant in southern India - paper . Swedish automobile firm Volvo AB has chosen India ' s southern Karnataka state for its proposed truck manufacturing unit , the Financial Express newspaper said on Tuesday . The company is expected to sign a memorandum of understanding with the state on October 17 , it quoted state industry minister R . V . Deshpande as saying . He said the Volvo factory would involve an investment of 13 billion rupees . It did not give more details . Company officials were not immedietely available for comment . Earlier this year , the Swedish firm received permission from the central government to set up a fully - owned subsidiary . - - Bombay newsroom + 91 - 22 - 265 9000 
